This paper deals with power distributions in committees, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT) and social choice theory (cs.DS). The algorithmic approach used in the paper involves integer linear programming, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses different power indices, which could be relevant to social influence analysis (cs.SI).
